SUPERSPORT United have confirmed the transfer of striker Jeremy Brockie to their Pretoria rivals Mamelodi Sundowns.The two Tshwane clubs have on Monday reached an agreement on Brockie's move to Sundowns. SuperSport confirmed the news on their official Twitter Account on Monday afternoon.In a club statement Matsatsantsa A Pitori CEO Stanley Matthews said they wish him well in his future.“It’s never easy to lose a key player like Jeremy, especially off the back of three great seasons with us in which we made 5 Cup Finals and he became the second highest scorer at the Club,” Mathews said"We also understand that at his age this is Jeremy’s last big move and opportunity to secure his financial future.”“Given that he has made a significant contribution to the Club on and off the field our Board have agreed to sanction his move to Mamelodi Sundowns and we wish him well in his future"Sundowns now will be looking forward to register Brockie for their 2018 CAF Champions League campaign as the Caf rules states that all teams taking part in the Champions League should register their squad by Monday and no other players can be added until August.